main event: A stationary aerial object was observed visually for 10 minutes at an altitude of 33,000 ft, traveling at an estimated speed of 750 mph over the Motobu Peninsula in Okinawa.
interesting points: The object was described as metallic and disc-shaped, with no visible means of propulsion.
The object appeared to hover, then accelerate and disappear.
The object was also tracked by radar for approximately 10 minutes after it started to move.
The radar operator making the observations was considered a superior observer and radar operator by his Commanding Officer.
Two F-86 and F-84E fighter jets were flying in the area but did not intercept the object.
